This paper discusses techniques for achieving secure geolocation over the Internet, which involves addressing adversarial tactics to manipulate geolocation. This topic falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and systems and control (cs.SY).
